From 976201dd5f597b7c25b9fc5ebeee382b5e6bf8fb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yangtao Li <frank.li@vivo.com>
Date: Tue, 11 Jul 2023 11:48:45 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: tegra: tegra20_ac97: Use devm_platform_get_and_ioremap_resource()
Git-commit: 976201dd5f597b7c25b9fc5ebeee382b5e6bf8fb
Patch-mainline: v6.6-rc1
References: jsc#PED-9993 jsc#PED-10202

Convert platform_get_resource(), devm_ioremap_resource() to a single
call to devm_platform_get_and_ioremap_resource(), as this is exactly
what this function does.

Signed-off-by: Yangtao Li <frank.li@vivo.com>
Acked-by: Thierry Reding <treding@nvidia.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20230711034846.69437-5-frank.li@vivo.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/soc/tegra/tegra20_ac97.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/tegra/tegra20_ac97.c b/sound/soc/tegra/tegra20_ac97.c
index a4073a746ae3..60e7df41c64c 100644
--- a/sound/soc/tegra/tegra20_ac97.c
+++ b/sound/soc/tegra/tegra20_ac97.c
@@ -328,8 +328,7 @@ static int tegra20_ac97_platform_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		goto err;
 	}
 
-	mem = platform_get_resource(pdev, IORESOURCE_MEM, 0);
-	regs = devm_ioremap_resource(&pdev->dev, mem);
+	regs = devm_platform_get_and_ioremap_resource(pdev, 0, &mem);
 	if (IS_ERR(regs)) {
 		ret = PTR_ERR(regs);
 		goto err_clk_put;
-- 
